example: You shouldn't be seeing this for any reason.
konachan:
Searches for an image on Konachan. Can only be used in NSFW channels. 

``x!konachan`` - Gets a random image from Konachan. 

``x!konachan [tag] [tag]`` - Gets an image with the specified tag(s). Ratings can also be specified (safe, questionable, or explicit).
danbooru:
Searches for an image on Danbooru. Can only be used in NSFW channels. 

``x!danbooru`` - Gets a random image from Danbooru. 

``x!danbooru [tag] [tag]`` - Gets an image with the specified tag(s). Ratings can also be specified (safe, questionable, or explicit).
yandere:
Searches for an image on Yande.re. Can only be used in NSFW channels. 

``x!yandere`` - Gets a random image from Yande.re. 

``x!yandere [tag] [tag]`` - Gets an image with the specified tag(s). Ratings can also be specified (safe, questionable, or explicit).
neko:
Gets an image from Nekos API. 

``x!neko`` - Gets a random image.
encode:
Encrypts your message. 

``x!encode <target> <message>`` - Encrypts the message using the target specified. Current targets include base64 and binary.
decode:
Decrypts your message. 

``x!decode <target> <message>`` - Decrypts the message using the target specified. Only base64 is supported.
hash:
Hashes your message. Not reversible. 

``x!hash <target> <message>`` - Hashes the message using the target specified. Current targets include md5, sha1, and sha256.
encipher:
Enciphers your message. 

``x!encipher <target> <message>`` - Enciphers the message using the target specified. Only supports caesar.
decipher:
Deciphers your message. 

``x!decpiher <target> <message>`` - Deciphers the message using the target specified. Only supports caesar.
reverse:
Reverses your message. 

``x!reverse <message>`` - Reverses your message.
8ball:
Ask Axiro a question and it will do its best to answer the question. 

``x!8ball <question>`` - Asks Axiro your question. 

``x!ask <question>`` - Same usage as above.
kiss:
Kisses the specified user, because kissing someone in real life either isn't enough or too hard. 

``x!kiss <player>`` - Kisses the specified player.
hug:
Hugs the specified user, because hugging someone in real life either isn't enough or you're just lonely. 

``x!hug <player>`` - Hugs the specified player.
tickle:
Tickles the specified user. Sounds fun. 

``x!tickle <player>`` - Tickles the specified player.
poke:
Pokes the specified user. Useful if you need to annoy someone. 

``x!poke <player>`` - Pokes the specified player.
slap:
Slaps the specified user, because they probably made you mad. 

``x!slap <player>`` - Slaps the specified user.
cuddle:
Cuddles the specified user. Keep them warm if you can. 

``x!cuddle <player>`` - Cuddles the specified user.
pat:
Pats the specified user. Why would you do that? 

``x!pat <player>`` - Pats the specified user.
urban:
Looks up a term on the Urban Dictionary. Can only be used in NSFW channels because definitions and examples might be NSFW. 

``x!urban <term>`` - Looks up the specified term.
meme: This feature has not been implemented yet.
randomquote:
Gets a random quote. 

``x!randomquote`` - Keep in mind that all of these quotes came out of a Reddit thread.
about:
Just run this command and I'll tell you about myself! 

``x!about`` - Self-explanatory.

``x!info`` - Alias, self-explanatory.
user:
I can tell you a few things about whatever user you choose. 

``x!user <player>`` - Self-explanatory.
invite:
Invite me to your server unless you don't like weirdness. 

``x!invite <player>`` - Self-explanatory.
suggest:
Got a suggestion? Send my creator one! 

``x!suggest <suggestion>`` - Don't troll my creator, please.
report:
Have you seen a bug? Tell my creator! 

``x!report <report>`` - Don't troll my creator, please.
github:
If you're a developer, absolutely run this command and check out my GitHub repository. 

``x!github`` - Self-explanatory.
upvote:
Upvoting Axiro means more people will notice it, and that speaks volumes. Unless you don't like Axiro. 

``x!upvote`` - Self-explanatory.
winner:
Are you a winner or is someone else a winner? 

``x!winner [player]`` - You can leave the player part blank and Axiro will declare a random person as a winner. You can mention a user to specifically target them.
loser:
Are you a loser or is someone else a loser? 

``x!loser [player]`` - You can leave the player part blank and Axiro will declare a random person as a loser. You can mention a user to specifically target them.
wegothim:
WE GOT HIM! 

``x!wegothim`` - I'm not being paid to promote "Last Week Tonight" by John Oliver or HBO. I'm just a fan.
kick:
Kicks the specified user. My pointy boots are on. 

``x!kick <player>`` - Self-explanatory.
ban:
Bans the specified user. Watch for Thor. 

``x!ban <player>`` - Self-explanatory.
prune:
Deletes a specified number of messages. Great for removing drama, and even better for enforcing censorship. 

``x!prune <# of messages to delete>`` - Please do not put in absurdly high numbers.
balance:
Checks how many chickens you have. 

``x!balance [player]`` - Self-explanatory.
pay:
Give someone chickens. This should be interesting. 

``x!pay <player> <amount>`` - Self-explanatory.
daily:
Get your daily chickens. 

``x!daily [player]`` - Specifying a player will give them your daily chickens.
gamble:
How is gambling chickens a good idea? 

``x!gamble <chickens>`` - You are very unlikely to get your chickens back, but here's how to use it.
raid:
Raiding farms for chickens is a bad idea, but who's stopping you? 

``x!raid`` - Watch out for farmers with pitchforks.
mine:
Mine at a local mine for some minerals. Will be traded for more chickens. 

``x!mine`` - Self-explanatory.
fish:
Go fishing at a lake. Whatever you catch gets traded for chickens. 

``x!fish`` - Self-explanatory.
play:
Play some music. The bot will go on YouTube and look. 

``x!play <name>`` - Play the track you're looking for. You can also put in the code to get the exact one. 
You need to be in a voice channel for this.
skip:
Skips the current track. 

``x!skip`` - Skips the current track being played.
stop:
Stop the bot from playing any more music. 

``x!stop`` - Self-explanatory.
pause:
Pause the bot. It can also be used to un-pause the bot. 

``x!pause`` - Self-explanatory.
queue:
Get a list of tracks that will be played. 

``x!queue`` - Self-explanatory.
repeat:
Set the current track on repeat. Can be used to turn off repeat. 

``x!repeat`` - Self-explanatory.
volume:
Set the volume of the bot. 

``x!volume <integer> - Default is 100 (max). Anything above that may cause distortion.
disconnect:
Disconnects the bot from its currently connected voice channel. 

``x!disconnect`` - Self-explanatory.
